{
  "texts": [
    "In the case where m ≲ κ, however, modes with a negative linear term may experience a transient tachyonic phase where w 2 < 0 and grow exponentially, i.e.",
    "σ ∼ e -iωt ∼ e |ω|t.",
    "Such a tachyonic growth is eventually halted by the finite mass, leading to w 2 ≈ m 2 > 0 in the IR limit k p → 0.",
    "Nevertheless, the exponential growth during the tachyonic period may overproduce particles and threaten perturbativity or even the inflationary background.",
    "Therefore, in favour of theoretical control, we will require m -κ ≳ -H throughout this paper."
  ]
}